oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tennessee Orphan Home in Columbia
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the front exterior of the Tennessee Orphan Home. Text on the top left corner of the photograph reads: "Tennessee Orphan Home, Columbia, Tenn. / Erected 1909 and 1910." The building was demolished in 1940.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Orphanages
